cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.AI 

The paper deals with 3D reconstruction from monocular image sequences, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the issue of severe occlusions, which is a challenge in graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a shape prior term to penalize irregularities in the time-varying structure, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper provides implementation details for heterogeneous platforms, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
